explain basic select /*+parallel(2)*/ count(distinct c1), c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9 from t0 group by c1, c2 with rollup order by c2;
Query Plan
=======================================================
|ID|OPERATOR                                 |NAME    |
-------------------------------------------------------
|0 |PX COORDINATOR MERGE SORT                |        |
|1 |└─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR                     |:EX10002|
|2 |  └─SORT                                 |        |
|3 |    └─HASH GROUP BY                      |        |
|4 |      └─EXCHANGE IN DISTR                |        |
|5 |        └─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR (HASH)      |:EX10001|
|6 |          └─HASH GROUP BY                |        |
|7 |            └─EXCHANGE IN DISTR          |        |
|8 |              └─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR (HASH)|:EX10000|
|9 |                └─HASH GROUP BY          |        |
|10|                  └─EXPANSION            |        |
|11|                    └─PX BLOCK ITERATOR  |        |
|12|                      └─TABLE FULL SCAN  |t0      |
=======================================================
